rComments: Great Professor! He keeps class interesting and makes you want to learn.  The textbook is an important aspect of his teaching and I found that his style of teaching was enjoyable!

Great prof. Highly entertaining, applies great analogous to help with difficult material.He can be random at times but he compliments the book and adds new material also - definetly not boring.  Looking forward to taking more classes with him.

Great prof. Fun and interesting; makes lectures bearable. Goes somewhat off-topic, but that's alright. He's a straight from the textbook type of prof, so make sure you know your text thoroughly. He also encourages you develop your own line of thought. If you've got a point to make on a test, back it up and you'll do fine.

In Gibo's class you need to learn the textbook on your own. He's wants you to develop your reasoning and evolutionary thinking: that's what lectures and tutorials are for. His tests assess how well you can think and reason in an evolutionary way. If you don't work on understanding textbook concepts at home his lectures will seem off topic.

the worst proessor I EVER had at any educational institution.His tests were easy, but very abstract.He didn't even seem to know the answers-probably why everyone did well.If you want a good grade take this class but if you want to LEARN ANYTHING forget it. you'll learn more about his dog, his life his bugs that have NOTHING to do with the course.
interesting but waaay off topic most of the time
